Discussion written to `discussion.md`. Three of four success criteria pass (λ₁ > 0, spectrum within ~30%, R² > 0.95); the gennMSE comparison criterion cannot be assessed from this directory alone. The sweep shows a broad basin of optimal LC weights at 1e-6 through 1e-3, with excellent Lyapunov recovery in that range and degradation at high LC. The main anomaly is duplicate runs with early-stopping variance, not the LC weight itself.
